50|$|In 1989, <b>Child</b> <b>Helpline</b> International founder Jeroo Billimoria {{worked closely}} with street {{children}} in India as a social worker. She gave the children her telephone number {{and told them to}} call if they needed any help, after which she received a large volume of contacts. Billimoria realised that these children needed someone to speak to and assist them. The idea of a toll-free number emerged and she set up Childline India - India's first and only <b>child</b> <b>helpline.</b>|$|R
